  "chapter": {
    "number": 16,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Reply of the Tongue Is from the LORD"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The plans of the heart belong to man,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the reply of the tongue is from the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All a man’s ways are pure in his own eyes,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but his motives are weighed out by the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Commit your works to the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your plans will be achieved.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD has made everything for His purpose—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even the wicked for the day of disaster.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Everyone who is proud in heart is detestable to the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "be assured that he will not go unpunished.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "By loving devotion and faithfulness iniquity is atoned for,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and by the fear of the LORD one turns aside from evil.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When a man’s ways please the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He makes even the man’s enemies live at peace with him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Better a little with righteousness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than great gain with injustice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A man’s heart plans his course,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the LORD determines his steps.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A divine verdict is on the lips of a king;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his mouth must not betray justice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Honest scales and balances are from the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all the weights in the bag are His concern.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Wicked behavior is detestable to kings,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for a throne is established through righteousness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Righteous lips are a king’s delight,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and he who speaks honestly is beloved.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The wrath of a king is a messenger of death,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a wise man will pacify it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When a king’s face brightens, there is life;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his favor is like a rain cloud in spring.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How much better to acquire wisdom than gold!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "To gain understanding is more desirable than silver.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The highway of the upright leads away from evil;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he who guards his way protects his life.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pride goes before destruction,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a haughty spirit before a fall.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It is better to be lowly in spirit among the humble",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than to divide the spoil with the proud.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whoever heeds instruction will find success,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4231
          },
          {
            "text": "and blessed is he who trusts in the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The wise in heart are called discerning,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and pleasant speech promotes instruction.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Understanding is a fountain of life to its possessor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the discipline of fools is folly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The heart of the wise man instructs his mouth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and adds persuasiveness to his lips.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pleasant words are a honeycomb,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "sweet to the soul and healing to the bones.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "There is a way that seems right to a man,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but its end is the way of death.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A worker’s appetite works for him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because his hunger drives him onward.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A worthless man digs up evil,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his speech",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4232
          },
          {
            "text": "is like a scorching fire.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A perverse man spreads dissension,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a gossip divides close friends.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A violent man entices his neighbor",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and leads him down a path that is not good.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who winks his eye devises perversity;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he who purses his lips is bent on evil.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Gray hair is a crown of glory;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it is attained along the path of righteousness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who is slow to anger is better than a warrior,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and he who controls his temper is greater than one who captures a city.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The lot is cast into the lap,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but its every decision is from the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 4231,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or Whoever speaks prudently will find what is good",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 16,
          "verse": 20
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 4232,
        "caller": "+",
